        "id": "kung-pao",
        "name": "Kung Pao Chicken",
        "hanzi": "宫保鸡丁",
        "pinyin": "gōngbǎo jīdīng",
        "categories": [
          "chicken",
          "spicy"
        ],
        "time": "30 min",
        "difficulty": "Easy",
        "image": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TeamDzX/hanyu-packs/main/images/food/kung-pao.jpg",
        "description": "A Sichuan classic of diced chicken stir-fried with peanuts, dried chilies and a glossy sweet-savoury sauce — quick, punchy and a takeaway favourite the world over.",
        "ingredients": [
          "2 chicken breasts, diced",
          "1/2 cup roasted peanuts",
          "8-10 dried red chilies",
          "3 spring onions, chopped",
          "2 cloves garlic + 1 tsp ginger, minced",
          "2 tbsp soy sauce, 1 tbsp black vinegar, 1 tsp sugar",
          "1 tsp cornflour + 1 tbsp water"
        ],
        "steps": [
          "Marinate the diced chicken in 1 tbsp soy sauce and the cornflour slurry for 10 minutes.",
          "Mix the remaining soy sauce, vinegar and sugar into a sauce.",
          "Stir-fry the chilies briefly in hot oil, then add the chicken and cook until golden.",
          "Add garlic, ginger and spring onion, then pour in the sauce and toss until glossy.",
          "Stir through the peanuts and serve with steamed rice."
        ],
