        "description": "Silky tofu in a fiery, numbing Sichuan sauce of doubanjiang and peppercorns. Comforting, bold and ready in minutes.",
        "ingredients": [
          "1 block soft tofu, cubed",
          "100g minced pork or beef (optional)",
          "1.5 tbsp doubanjiang (chili bean paste)",
          "1 tsp ground Sichuan peppercorn",
          "2 cloves garlic + 1 tsp ginger, minced",
          "1 cup stock, 1 tsp cornflour slurry",
          "Spring onion to finish"
        ],
        "steps": [
          "Gently blanch the tofu cubes in salted water, then drain.",
          "Fry the mince until browned, add doubanjiang, garlic and ginger until fragrant and red.",
          "Pour in the stock, slide in the tofu and simmer gently for 4-5 minutes.",
          "Thicken with the cornflour slurry, sprinkle with Sichuan pepper and spring onion."
